node.text: On the coast of Portugal, Gordon Ramsay visits one of the most unique vineyards on the planet where the vines grow in the sand. A new season of Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted airs Monday, May 31 at 9/8c.

node.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted – A Vineyard in the Sand

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on August 30, 2021. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text: Photo by Robbie Shone @shonephoto / During the Greenland Caves Project's 2019 expedition, we explored Kate’s Cove cave as far as we could. We went down a steep boulder pile into the depths of the cave. The floor was strewn with rocks and the walls were cold. We had never been in a cave before where the rocks were so cold. The expedition medic even suggested I had frostnip at one point! After about 80 meters (262 feet), the bouldery floor gave way to a narrow slot. Pictured here, Chris bridges his way over the top of the slot. We climbed down to see if it led to a way on. It got colder and colder, and at its deepest point it was minus 17.1°C (1.2°F). Could this be one of the coldest caves in the world? Who knows.

node.text:
Photo by @daisygilardini / Scoresby Sound is one of the biggest fjord systems in the world. Its main body is 110 kilometers (roughly 70 miles) long and spreads out into a series of side fjords and islets that cover some 38,000 square kilometers (roughly 15,000 square miles). The large glaciers found along these fjords produce a massive amount of icebergs. The icebergs in the fjords are particularly active, as the system creates its own circular gyre currents. The icebergs are constantly moving as they're flushed out into open water.
Follow me @daisygilardini for more images and behind-the-scenes stories. #greenland #scoresbysund #iceberg #alpenglow #conservation

node.text:
Photo by @mattborowick / The Slate River winds below Purple Mountain in this amazing place that is a nature photographer's dream. Crested Butte, Colorado, sits around 9,000 feet (2,743 meters) in elevation, making it higher than most U.S. cities. Acclimating to the elevation is often a tall order for visitors. Staying hydrated and easing into it is the best way to keep yourself healthy. 
Please follow @mattborowick for more pictures like this. #colorado #mountains #nature #adventure #crestedbutte

node.text:
Photo by @DaisyGilardini / A beautiful sunrise illuminates the Cascade Range in British Columbia, Canada. The first rule in photography is to be there. Obviously, if you aren't there, you won’t be able to get the picture. Over the years I've learned that no matter what the weather forecast is, you have to be on location and ready to shoot. Quite often it's in bad weather that you get the nicest images. You never know when the light might peek through the fog. And when it does, the scene might be really spectacular and much more dramatic than it is during clear skies.
During my recent trip to Manning Provincial Park, we woke up at 4 a.m. to reach the summit on time for the sunrise. Thick fog was waiting for us. Instead of turning back, we decided to find a good flower meadow. We were soon rewarded with the sun peeking through the fog, creating this wonderful moment. 
Follow me @daisygilardini for more images and behind-the-scenes stories. #sunrise #britishcolumbia #CascadeMountains #landscapephotography

node.text: Photo by @MichaelGeorge / The Japanese Hill-and-Pond Garden at the Brooklyn Botanic Garden has a pavilion overlooking a koi pond, with a torii gate in the background. It is the perfect spot to take a moment of rest, as this visitor has, to read a book or to dawdle around on your phone. In the spring, the sunset light hits the pavilion in such a way that it begins to glow. For more photos and writing from my travels, follow along @MichaelGeorge. #bbg #brooklynbotanicgarden #japanesepavilion #sunset #Brooklyn

Some scenes just give you a feeling—one that you hope to transmit through an always imperfect image. For more journeys inward and outward, follow me @joshuacogan. #Bali #Ubud

node.text:
Photo by @francescolastrucci / Pilgrims take a blessing by one of the fountains of the Pura Tirta Empul (Temple of the Holy Spring). The Balinese visit this place of worship to purify themselves under the sacred waters of the pools, fed by the springs flowing from the side of the sacred mountain. Built in 962 and dedicated to Vishnu, the structure is made up of a set of temples near the village of Manukaya in central Bali. The persistent scent of incense burning on offer to the gods and the bright colors of the flowers on the fountains make the experience inside the temple highly evocative and mystical. 
Follow me @francescolastrucci for more places, daily life, and stories around the world. #bali #indonesia #rituals #dailylife

node.text: Photo by @bertiegregory / Puffins can fly up to 55 miles (89 kilometers) an hour, flapping their wings 400 times a minute! This rapid wing beat and lack of gliding means they have a pretty frantic appearance when they zoom past. Follow @bertiegregory for more wildlife adventures. #puffin #britishwildlife #cute #fishing #wildlifephotography
